FBIS3-26808 "drchi031_q_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 Southwest Region Tibet Chairman Views Reform, Economic Development OW0902131794 Lhasa Tibet Television Network in Mandarin 1200 GMT 8 Feb 94 OW0902131794 Lhasa Tibet Television Network Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report; from the "Regional News Hookup" program] [Excerpts] Viewers, following are excerpts of Autonomous Regional Chairman Gyaincain Norbu's speech delivered at the 1994 Spring Festival and Tibetan New Year gathering. [passage omitted] The maintenance of social stability is the prerequisite for the promotion of reform, opening up, and economic development. Hence, according to the law we must adhere to the principle of fostering both material progress and cultural and ideological progress, and must be firm in cracking down on hostile elements simultaneously involved in splitting the motherland, creating riots and trouble, and destabilizing the situation. [passage omitted]
